{{Infobox person | name = Dag Østerberg | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1938|11|9|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Trondheim]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|2017|2|22|1938|11|9|df=y}} | death_place = | monuments = | residence = | nationality = Norwegian | other_names = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = Sociologist, philosopher and musicologist | years_active = | employer = [[University of Oslo]] | organization = | agent = | known_for = | notable_works = | style = | influences = | influenced = | home_town = | television = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = [[Erling Østerberg]] | relatives = | awards = }}
'''Dag Østerberg''' (9 November [[1938 in Norway|1938]] &ndash; 22 February [[2017 in Norway|2017]]) was a Norwegian sociologist, philosopher and musicologist.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abcnyheter.no/nyheter/2017/02/24/195280265/dag-osterberg-er-dod|title=Dag Østerberg er død - ABC Nyheter|date=24 February 2017|work=abcnyheter.no|accessdate=24 February 2017}}</ref>
He was born in [[Trondheim]] to police officer [[Erling Østerberg]] and Jørgine Sofie Kleven. He was a central contributor to the so-called [[positivism]] debate in the 1960s and 1970s. From 1981 to 1991 he was appointed professor in sociology at the [[University of Oslo]]. Among his works are ''Metasosiologisk Essay'' from 1963, ''Makt og materiell'' from 1971, and a biography of [[Jean-Paul Sartre]] from 1993.<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Dag Østerberg |encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Ragnvald |last=Kalleberg |authorlink= |editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]] |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo|url=https://nbl.snl.no/Dag_Østerberg |language=Norwegian |accessdate=20 May 2015 }}</ref><ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|title=Dag Østerberg |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|first= |last= |authorlink= |editor-last=Godal | editor-first=Anne Marit | editor-link=Anne Marit Godal |publisher=Norsk nettleksikon |location=Oslo |url=https://snl.no/Dag_Østerberg |language=Norwegian|accessdate=20 May 2015}}</ref> His 1966 work '' Forståelsesformer. Et filosofisk bidrag'' (Forms of Understanding: A Philosophical Contribution) was selected for the [[Norwegian Sociology Canon]] in 2009–2011.
